Head transverse, HW/HL: 1.07-1.13; puncturation on average more distinct; surface often (but not always!) with shallower microsculpture and more shine. Eyes larger and clearly more prominent (
Fig. 31
), usually longer than postocular region in dorsal view; EyL/PoL: 0.75-0.90 (
Fig. 32
).

